Kim Jong Il inspects army unit 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 18 (KCNA) - General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected unit no. 1224 of the Korean People's Army (KPA) on sunday.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He was accompanied by vice Marshals Jo Myong Rok, Kim Yong Chun and Kim Il Chol and general officers of the KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The visiting party also included secretaries Kim Kuk Thae and Kim Yong Sun and first vice department directors of the party central committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   After receiving a salute, he learned about how the unit was performing its duty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He saw soldiers under training, and gave the unit important tasks to increase its fighting capacity in every way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He looked round the education room, bedroom, dining room and other places and highly appreciated their revolutionary way of work and life, noting that they were managing the unit as methodically as the anti-Japanese guerrillas had done. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Warm comradeship for soldiers is one of the noble traits that characterize the commanding officers of the revolutionary army of Korea, he said, and urged all the commanding officers to pay deep attention to every detail of the soldiers' life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He saw an art performance of soldiers and said that the KPA, which is ready to defend the party and revolution, country and people at the cost of life, is a model of revolutionary army in ideological, spiritual, moral and all other aspects. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He gave the unit's soldiers a pair of binoculars, a machine gun and an automatic rifle as gifts and had a picture taken with them.

National seminar on Juche idea in Uganda
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 18 (KCNA) -- A national seminar on the Juche idea for the building of independent and peaceful Uganda was held in Kampala, Uganda, on October 7 under the sponsorship of the Ugandan National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea to mark the second anniversary of the great leader Kim Jong Il's election as General Secretary of the Worker's Party of Korea and the 54th anniversary of the foundation of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present were figures of political, social and academic circles and members of the Juche idea study groups and friendship organisations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Baguma Isoke, Minister of State of the Ministry of Water, Land and Environment and chairman of the Ugandan National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea, in his opening address said that the seminar will undoubtedly be one more landmark in accomplishing the historic cause of building a prosperous new society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Chango Machyo, senior advisor to the president and director of the board of the International Institute of the Juche Idea, made a report entitled "let us build independent and peaceful Uganda," which was followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the seminar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A declaration entitled "let us build independent and peaceful new society under the banner of Juche" was adopted at the seminar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The declaration said that they will hold higher the great Juche idea, founded by the President Kim Il Sung and developed in depth by Marshal Kim Jong Il, as an immortal banner guiding the 21st century, so as to vigorously struggle for building in this land a prosperous new society in which the desire of independence and the idea of peace are realized. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The declaration resolutely denounced the U.S. and reactionaries for all their moves to isolate socialist Korea and extended full support and firm solidarity to the just struggle of the Korean people to achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country and build a powerful socialist state.

Floral baskets to Kim Jong Il
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 18 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received floral baskets from foreign figures and organs on October 8 and 9 on the occasions of the second anniversary of his election and the 54th anniversary of the foundation of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The baskets were sent to Korean embassies in respective countries by Youssef Wali, general secretary of the National Democratic Party and vice-premier of Egypt, Rifaat Es-Said, general secretary of the National Progressive Unionist Party of Egypt, the director of the Itribko International Export Trading Company, the director of the Sakari Machine and Tool Trading Company, the ex-director of the general bureau of film festival of the Ministry of Culture of Egypt, the director of the exhibition department of the Ministry of Culture of Egypt, the newspaper Al Siyassi and the commission for external affairs of the c.c., the Lao People's Revolutionary Party.

Foreigners visit DPRK embassies
   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 18 (KCNA) -- Cuban woman lawyer Candelaria Rodriguez paid a congratulatory visit to the DPRK embassy in Havana on October 9 on the occasions of the second anniversary of the great leader Kim Jong Il's election as General Secretary of the Worker's Party of Korea and the 54th birthday of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She laid a basket of flowers and made a bow before the portraits of the President Kim Il Sung and Marshal Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She said that Kim Il Sung was the most benevolent and tender-hearted father of the people, a great leader and great man and that even if thousands of years pass by, he will always live in the hearts of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Saying that Kim Jong Il's long life in good health is her happiness, she stressed that the workers' party, the government and the people of Korea led by him will always emerge victorious. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Meanwhile, chief of information of the organization of socialists in the Mediterranean, paid a congratulatory visit to the DPRK embassy in Libya on October 11 and wished Kim Jong Il a long life in good health and the Korean people progress and prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Hoping that under the leadership of Kim Jong Il the WPK and the Korean people would achieve greater success in building a powerful nation, he expressed support to the Korean people's cause of national reunification.

Gathering of crew of foreign ships
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 18 (KCNA) -- Crewmen  of foreign ships gathered at Nampho port on Oct. 16 to praise the leadership feats of the President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il on the occasions of the 54th anniversary of the foundation of the Worker's Party of Korea and the 73rd anniversary of the formation of the "Down-with-Imperialism Union" (DIU). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present were crew of the Chinese ship Tai Bai Hai and Cambodian-flagged ship Sophia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Captains and crewmen made speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Speakers said that the WPK took its historical roots when the DIU was formed by Kim Il Sung, a veteran leader of the world revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The WPK, founded by the President on October 10, 1945, has been strengthened and developed into invincible revolutionary party under the wise leadership of the Marshal, they stressed, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people, who are rallied close around the Marshal, holding the President in high esteem as the eternal leader, are vigorously advancing, not yielding to the political and military pressure and isolation and suffocation moves of the imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Under the leadership of the Marshal the WPK will glorify its name as an ever-victorious party and the party of Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the gathering. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Before the gathering the participants laid bouquets before the statue of Kim Il Sung in Nampho and made a bow.

S. Korean students protest U.S.'s massacre
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 18 (KCNA) -- About 1,000 students under the South Korean Federation of University Student Councils Saturday held a rally and demonstration in protest against the brutal massacre committed by U.S. aggression troops at the start of the Korean War, according to a foreign press report from Seoul. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At the rally, they chanted the slogan "we protest the Rogun-ri massacre" and waved hundreds of small yellow flags with the same message. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They marched through downtown Seoul, distributing leaflets. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The demonstrators reiterated their demand that Washington withdraw U.S. troops to ease tension on the divided Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They demanded that South Korean rulers abolish the "security law", a tool of fascist suppression.

Huichon Revolutionary Site
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 18 (KCNA) -- The Huichon Revolutionary Site is located in Huichon city, Jagang Province, the nation's leading machine-tool producer. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The site is associated with immortal feats of the President Kim Il Sung. He came to Huichon and instructed workers to build a machine-tool producing base foreseeing the victory in the Fatherland Liberation War (June 1950-july 1953). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   There are a statue of the President and a historic monument, revolutionary museum and open-air revolutionary sites. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Huichon Revolutionary Museum has 22 rooms which are devoted to more than 800 photos, data and historic relics telling the visitors that the President visited Huichon on more than 20 occasions and gave on-site guidance to over 90 units and General Secretary Kim Jong Il visited several places of Huichon on a guidance mission on 7 occasions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A room has a mock-up of 10,000 machine-tools showing how the President kindled the torch of a new technical innovation and led the production of machine-tools from February, Juche 60 (1971) to April, Juche 61 (1972). The museum is recently supplemented with 80 more pieces of photos, data and historic relics showing Kim Jong Il's on-site guidance to the Huichon General Machine Tool Plant, the February 26 Factory, the Youth Electric Complex, the Huichon Silk Mill and the Huichon Hotel in June and October last year, drawing the attention of visitors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Preserved in their original state in the Kumsugol and Jisindong revolutionary sites are tile-roofed earthen houses and other historic relics used by the President during his on-site guidance to Huichon.

Projected "foal eagle" war maneuvers
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 18 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun in a signed commentary today dismisses the projected "foal eagle" joint military exercises in South Korea as a test operation to militarily threaten and stifle the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Though these maneuvers are described by the United States as an "annual event,"  the exercises are to be participated in by its troops present in South Korea, a naval task force of the U.S. 7th fleet and huge combatant forces in the Asia-Pacific region and the U.S. mainland and hundreds of thousands of armed forces of the "ROK". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The projected U.S. war maneuvers are a clear indication that it is unwilling to implement the DPRK-U.S. agreed framework and ease tension on the Korean peninsula and ensure peace there, the commentary says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   There is no doubt that the war maneuvers will lead the situation on the peninsula to a danger point and aggravate the DPRK-U.S. belligerent relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Their madcap saber-rattling compels us to heighten vigilance and further strengthen our self-defensive posture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The United States must be wholly responsible for the adverse impact the war maneuvers will have on the situation on the Korean peninsula and the DPRK-U.S. relations.

Classic work that calls for carrying forward tradition of WPK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 18 (KCNA) -- 17 years have passed since General Secretary Kim Jong Il made public the classic work "the Worker's Party of Korea is a Juche-Type Revolutionary Party which Inherited the Glorious Tradition of the DIU". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The work, published on October 17, Juche 71 (1982), comprehensively clarified the character and mission of the WPK  that has inherited the tradition of the "DIU" and clearly laid down issues of principle in building a revolutionary party in our times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The idea of adhering to the tradition of Juche occupies an important place among the ideas and theories expounded in the work.  To  steadily glorify the WPK as a party which is carrying forward the tradition of Juche by upholding the idea and theory of the President Kim Il Sung and the revolutionary achievements accomplished by him, and carrying out the party construction and activities as the President did is the prevailing idea of this work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Rodong Sinmun yesterday in a signed article dedicated to this day said that the WPK is now displaying its might as a revolutionary party which is steadfastly  carrying forward the tradition of Juche and as a dignified and authoritative party shining with the august name of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Marshal Kim Jong Il's leadership over the adherence to  the tradition of Juche is wise in that he is steering the party construction and activities  guided by the President's idea and theory and firmly upholding the achievements and experience  gained by him in the struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Noting that all the activities of the WPK are aimed to uphold the achievements and experience of the President, the article stressed:  It is the result of the wise leadership of the Marshal Kim Jong Il that the WPK has grown to be a revolutionary party which is carrying forward the President's achievements  100 per cent.

KCNA assails S. Korean "government's" worst bugging
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 18 (KCNA) -- Such human right abuse as violating privacy of communications has become more rampant since the appearance of the self-proclaimed "people's government" in South Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Over 8,700 bugging  cases were reportedly committed by the South Korean prosecution, police, "Intelligence Service" and military investigation organ last year and at least 1,700 cases of them  bugged by use of cellular phones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   More than 500 cases of bugging by these phones  have been perpetrated in the first half of the year alone.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This  eloquently proves that the "government" in South Korea is the  world's worst  perpetrator of bugging of communications. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The violation of communication privacy glaringly reveals a total absence of democracy in South Korea, a barren land of human rights as it is a breach of elementary freedom of correspondence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The authorities of the "Intelligence Service", "defence security command", the prosecution and police regularly wire-tap all the telephone messages and provide or receive information about private communications. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Under this alarming situation the people cannot freely communicate with each other. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The rulers of the "people's government" are  fully accountable for this dreadful atmosphere where one can neither say nor hear the truth as every movement of the people is watched and investigated and their communication is bugged by a dense network of such suppressive machines as the "Intelligence Service", prosecutor office and police. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This year, they have purchased 175 communication bugging equipment and  delivered them to the repressive  machines. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The "people's government" clamors about "guarantee of human rights" whenever an  opportunity presents  itself, but nothing has changed and conspiratorial plots against the progressive forces and human right abuses have become more pronounced. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They are advertising that "solution"  has been sought, talking nonsense that "checking"  and "punishment" of perpetrators of bugging by  individuals or organizations would prevent human right abuses. But this is nothing but a window-dressing to hide their true colors as the worst perpetrators of bugging. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The South Korean rulers should immediately stop their dastardly bugging of communication, a most serious violation of democracy and human rights.

Foundation day of DIU observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 18 (KCNA) -- 73 years have passed since the Down-with-Imperialism Union (DIU), the first revolutionary vanguard organization of Juche type, was formed in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Worker's Party of Korea regards the DIU as its roots and its formation as the new starting-point and origin of the Korean communist movement and the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It was not until the President Kim Il Sung's creation of the DIU on October 17, Juche 15 (1926) that the Korean people greeted a new era of waging their revolutionary struggle on the principle of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The President wrote in his reminiscences that the immediate task of the DIU was to defeat Japanese imperialism and achieve the liberation and independence of Korea, and its final objective was to build socialism and communism in Korea and, furthermore, destroy all imperialism and build communism throughout the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The formation of the DIU was the historic declaration heralding a new beginning of the Korean revolution and the starting-point of building the party of the Juche type, the revolutionary party of new type, in our country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The DIU's great exploits remain shining in the history of the Korean revolution because the President formed and built it as a powerful revolutionary organization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The WPK has performed great feats shining in the century and grown to be a revolutionary party of Juche type which has attained its perfect cohesion and unity and accumulated a wealth of experience. Such a glorious struggle originated from the DIU. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The history of the WPK that began with the DIU as its roots testifies to the truth that the party's greatness is precisely the greatness of the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The banner of the DIU will fly high forever  as  the WPK is led by the great leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean revolution had to weather out many rigorous trials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   But, he has overcome difficulties with his strong will, strengthened the party and increased its leadership role, bringing about an uninterrupted upsurge in the revolution and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The WPK is now wisely leading the cause of building a powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The immortal exploits of Kim Jong Il, who has developed and strengthened the WPK as a revolutionary party of Juche type, the party of Kim Il Sung that has carried forward the tradition of the DIU, will shine forever.

KCNA slams S. Korean authorities' anti-north diatribe
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 18 (KCNA) -- Some private papers of Ethiopia reportedly said that the DPRK dispatched  missile and landmine experts to Ethiopia, quoting an article of the South Korean paper "Korea Times," and an Ethiopian language program of the German radio aired the same message. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This is a sheer lie dreamed up by those who felt the need to spread the rumour that the DPRK is militarily involved in the dispute between Ethiopia and Eritrea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is our invariable and principled stand that the disputes between developing countries should be solved peacefully through talks and negotiations between those concerned in their mutual interests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The dispute between Ethiopia and Eritrea is the problem that must be solved by themselves under any circumstances. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
One can, therefore, hardly imagine that the DPRK may be involved in the dispute. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The DPRK, which regards independence, peace and friendship as noble tenet of its foreign policy, has never intervened in any regional disputes  nor  got involved in other incidents to make them complicated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This notwithstanding,  the "Korea Times," ill-famed for hackwork and tricks, spread such a whopping lie arousing our indignation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Needless to say, the "Korea Times" released the false report on the basis of misinformation provided by the "Intelligence Service," headquarters for anti-north operations, to carry out its order. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This diatribe  is nothing but a sinister attempt to drive a wedge in the good friendly relations between the DPRK and African countries and tarnish the international image of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   We sincerely hope the earliest  possible realization of the positive proposal and efforts of the Organization of African Unity and the African countries to seek a peaceful solution to the dispute. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Those who groundlessly slander others will be wholly accountable for the consequences of their smear campaign. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The South Korean authorities are well advised to properly judge the trend of the times and the desire of the nation and stop at once their foolish anti-north diatribe.

Stamps on Jong Song Ok issued
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 18 (KCNA) -- Stamps on the world marathon queen Jong Song Ok have been issued in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As already known to the world, Jong Song Ok is a praiseworthy daughter of the nation who displayed the dignity and spirit of Kim Il Sung's Korea by placing first in the women's marathon race of the 7th World Athletics Championships. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The sheet issued this time by the Ministry of Post and Telecommunications depicts her strong fighting spirit and dignified appearance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The sheet carries the mark of the championships under the letters "winner Jong Song Ok of the 7th World Athletics Championships" with the DPRK flag for a background. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
And it depicts  Jong  leaving the start line and making a report about her victory to General Secretary Kim Jong Il, after emerging as winner by running, picturing him in her mind. This vividly represents the faith and will of the Korean people dynamically hastening the second grand chollima march, overcoming all trials and hardships. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   There is also a stamp carrying the picture of Jong arriving in the homeland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The ministry also issued postcards, envelops and stamp book depicting her.

Wreaths laid before grave of Ri Po Ik
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 18 (KCNA) -- Party and state leading officials, servicemen of the people's army and working people today laid wreaths before the grave of Ri Po Ik, an ardent patriot, in the Mangyongdae Revolutionary Site on the occasion of the 40th anniversary of her death. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Laid before her grave was a wreath sent by General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were Yang Hyong Sop, Kim Ki Nam, Kwak Pom Gi, Kim Ryong Yon and other officials of party and power organs, ministries, national institutions and KPA generals and  soldiers and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Amid the playing of wreath-laying music wreaths  were laid in the names of the Central Committee of the WPK, ministries, national institutions, KPA units, educational, health and press institutions and party and  power organs, factories and farms in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The participants observed  a moment's silence in memory of her immortal life characterized by love for the country, nation and people.
